    "catalysts": [],
    "industrial_process_notes": "Stephanie Kwolek developed the first para-aramid fiber at DuPont, commercialized as Kevlar in 1973; the term 'aramid' was introduced in 1972 and formally recognized as a generic fiber category by the US Federal Trade Commission in 1974. Akzo introduced the competing fiber Twaron in 1978. World para-aramid production was estimated at 41,000 tonnes/year in 2002, growing 5-10% annually.",
